The paper deals with developing efficient algorithms for sorting strings on distributed-memory parallel machines, which involves communication and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves data structures and algorithms for sorting, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves communication volume reduction, which suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
